 Miyuki warms up to Tatsuya, and Tatsuya develops a friendship with major Kazama Harunobu. During that time, an invasion by the Great Asian Alliance results in Hoonami's death, and is resolved with Tatsuya's matter detonation. Back in the present, Maya warns Tatsuya that his matter detonation has garnered the attention of the United States of North America (USNA).\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |9\n|style=\"text-align: left\"|{{Nihongo foot|Visitor Arc (I)|\u6765\u8a2a\u8005\u7de8\uff1c\u4e0a\uff1e|Raih\u014dsha-hen (J\u014d)|group=Jp.}}\n|March 10, 2013<ref name=\"LN 9\">{{cite web| url=http://dengekibunko.jp/newreleases/978-4-04-891423-9/| script-title=ja:\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u52a3\u7b49\u751f 9| publisher=[[Dengeki Bunko]]| accessdate=August 4, 2015| language=Japanese}}</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-4-04-891423-9}}\n|September 18, 2018<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.b2c.hachettebookgroup.com/titles/none/the-irregular-at-magic-high-school-vol-9-light-novel/9781975327149/?yen|title=The Irregular at Magic High School, Vol. 9 (light novel) |website=[[Yen Press]] |accessdate=April 3, 2018}}</ref>\n|{{ISBN|978-1-975-32714-9}}\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF; text-align: left\"|Following a black hole experiment in the USNA, deserters from the military flee to Japan. The Stars military unit pursue in order to execute the deserters and investigate the magician behind matter detonation. [[#Angelina Kudo Shields|Angelina Kudo Shields]] infiltrates First High to spy on Tatsuya and Miyuki. As the story progresses, the deserters' abnormal abilities and activities garner the interest of Japan's magic clans. After confronting Angelina and one of the deserters, Tatsuya trades his silence for her information.\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |10\n|style=\"text-align: left\"|{{Nihongo foot|Visitor Arc (II)|\u6765\u8a2a\u8005\u7de8\uff1c\u4e2d\uff1e|Raih\u014dsha-hen (Ch\u016b)|group=Jp.}}\n|June 7, 2013<ref name=\"LN 10\">{{cite web| url=http://dengekibunko.jp/newreleases/978-4-04-891609-7/| script-title=ja:\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u52a3\u7b49\u751f 10| publisher=[[Dengeki Bunko]]| accessdate=August 4, 2015| language=Japanese}}</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-4-04-891609-7}}\n|December 18, 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.b2c.hachettebookgroup.com/titles/none/the-irregular-at-magic-high-school-vol-10-light-novel/9781975327163/?yen|title=The Irregular at Magic High School, Vol. 10 (light novel) - Yen Press|website=www.b2c.hachettebookgroup.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-11}}</ref>\n|{{ISBN|978-1-975-32716-3}}\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF; text-align: left\"|Tatsuya deduces the deserters are possessed by sentient psychic energy beings which came from the magic dimension during the black hole experiment and are dubbed as parasites. When one of the parasites enters First High, it is defeated by Tatsuya's group and possess the android known as [[#Pixy|Pixy]]; the parasite is imprinted with Honoka's feelings and decides to serve Tatsuya. Meanwhile, the USNA suspect Tatsuya is the one behind matter detonation and orders Angelina to assassinate him.\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |11\n|style=\"text-align: left\"|{{Nihongo foot|Visitor Arc (III)|\u6765\u8a2a\u8005\u7de8\uff1c\u4e0b\uff1e|Raih\u014dsha-hen (Ge)|group=Jp.}}\n|August 10, 2013<ref name=\"LN 11\">{{cite web| url=http://dengekibunko.jp/newreleases/978-4-04-891610-3/| script-title=ja:\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u52a3\u7b49\u751f 11| publisher=[[Dengeki Bunko]]| accessdate=August 4, 2015| language=Japanese}}</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-4-04-891610-3}}\n|March 19, 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.b2c.hachettebookgroup.com/titles/none/the-irregular-at-magic-high-school-vol-11-light-novel/9781975327187/?yen|title=The Irregular at Magic High School, Vol. 11 (light novel) - Yen Press|website=www.b2c.hachettebookgroup.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-11}}</ref>\n|{{ISBN|978-1-975-32718-7}}\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF; text-align: left\"|Tatsuya defeats A