one/the-irregular-at-magic-high-school-vol-14-light-novel/9781975332471/?yen|title=The Irregular at Magic High School, Vol. 14 (light novel) - Yen Press|website=www.b2c.hachettebookgroup.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-18}}</ref>\n|{{ISBN|978-1-975-33247-1}}\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF; text-align: left\"|Tatsuya is ordered to participate in the hunt for Zhou. Several clues reveal Zhou is hidden by the [[traditional values|traditionalist]] magicians. Tatsuya requests aid from the Kudo clan who are knowledgeable about the traditionalist. Led by Minoru Kudo, Tatsuya's group confronts the traditionalists in [[Nara, Nara|Nara]] but are unable to find Zhou, leaving [[Kyoto]] as the remaining location. Meanwhile, the Saegusa head sends an assassin to kill Zhou in order to destroy any evidence of their coalition. The assassin is killed instead, spurring Mayumi to request Tatsuya's aid in finding his killer.\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |15\n|style=\"text-align: left\"|{{Nihongo foot|Ancient City Insurrection Arc (II)|\u53e4\u90fd\u5185\u4e71\u7de8\uff1c\u4e0b\uff1e|Koto Nairan-hen (Ge)|group=Jp.}}\n|January 10, 2015<ref name=\"LN 15\">{{cite web| url=http://dengekibunko.jp/newreleases/978-4-04-869167-3/| script-title=ja:\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u52a3\u7b49\u751f 15| publisher=[[Dengeki Bunko]]| accessdate=August 4, 2015| language=Japanese}}</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-4-04-869167-3}}\n|March 24, 2020<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.b2c.hachettebookgroup.com/titles/none/the-irregular-at-magic-high-school-vol-15-light-novel/9781975332495/?yen|title=The Irregular at Magic High School, Vol. 15 (light novel) - Yen Press|website=www.b2c.hachettebookgroup.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-18}}</ref>\n|{{ISBN|978-1-975-33249-5}}\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF; text-align: left\"|Tatsuya and his companions investigate Zhou's whereabouts in Kyoto and eventually catch and corner him. Zhou then commits suicide, proclaiming someone else will resume his duties. Tatsuya's success forces members of the Yotsuba who despise him to allow Maya to proceed with her plans.\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |16\n|style=\"text-align: left\"|{{Nihongo foot|Yotsuba Succession Arc|\u56db\u8449\u7d99\u627f\u7de8 |Yotsuba Keish\u014d-hen|group=Jp.}}\n|May 9, 2015<ref name=\"LN 16\">{{cite web| url=http://dengekibunko.jp/newreleases/978-4-04-865116-5/| script-title=ja:\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u52a3\u7b49\u751f 16| publisher=[[Dengeki Bunko]]| accessdate=August 4, 2015| language=Japanese}}</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-4-04-865116-5}}\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF; text-align: left\"|Miyuki is summoned to the Yotsuba New Years meeting to commemorate her as the next head of the clan. Several [[bunke]] members of the clan attempt to derail Miyuki's attendance as her succession will elevate Tatsuya's status. Upon their arrival, Miyuki is appointed as the next head, and the origins of Tatsuya and Miyuki's birth is revealed. While they are born from the same [[gamete]]s, Miyuki was genetically modified to act as a seal to his powers. In the next meeting, Maya announces Tatsuya's engagement to Miyuki.\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |17\n|style=\"text-align: left\"|{{Nihongo foot|Master Clan Conference Arc (I)|\u5e2b\u65cf\u4f1a\u8b70\u7de8\uff1c\u4e0a\uff1e|Shizoku Kaigi-hen (J\u014d)|group=Jp.}}\n|August 8, 2015<ref name=\"LN 17\">{{cite web| url=http://dengekibunko.jp/newreleases/978-4-04-865313-8/| script-title=ja:\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u52a3\u7b49\u751f 17| publisher=[[Dengeki Bunko]]| accessdate=August 9, 2015| language=Japanese}}</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-4-04-865313-8}}\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF; text-align: left\"|Tatsuya and Miyuki adjust to their daily life as their ties to the Yotsuba and engagement have become public knowledge. Meanwhile, a meeting between the master clans take place where they discuss three topics: possible members of the master clan, Tatsuya and Miyuki's marriage, and Saegusa's coalition with the deceased Zhou. Jiedo Heigu, the leader of the organized crime group and Zhou's boss, initiates several bombings against the master clans in order to discredit the magic community.\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |18\n|style=\"text-align: left\"|{{Nihongo foot|Master Clan Conference Arc (II)|\u5e2b\u65cf\u4f1a\u8b70\u7de8\uff1c\u4e2d\uff1e|Shizoku Kaigi-hen (Ch\u016b)|group=Jp.}}\n|November 10, 2015<ref name=\"LN 18\">{{cite web| url=http://dengekibunko.jp/newreleases/978-4-04-865512-5/| script-title=ja:\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u52a3\u7b49\u751f 18| publisher=[[Dengeki Bunko]]| accessdate=October 26, 2015| language=Japanese}}</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-4-04-865512-5}}\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF; text-align: left\"|Jiedo's plan succeeds, inciting several [[hate crime]]s towards magicians throughout the world. The master clans makes plans to quell public outrage as well as attempts to capture Jiedo. The volume ends with Miyuki and her friends defending themselves against a group of anti-magicians.\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |19\n|style=\"text-align: left\"|{{Nihongo foot|Master Clan Conference Arc (III)|\u5e2b\u65cf\u4f1a\u8b70\u7de8\uff1c\u4e0b\uff1e|Shizoku Kaigi-hen (Ge)|group=Jp.}}\n|March 10, 2016<ref name=\"LN 19\">{{cite web|url=http://dengekibunko.jp/newreleases/978-4-04-865809-6/|script-title=ja:\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u52a3\u7b49\u751f 19|publisher=[[Dengeki Bunko]]| accessdate=March 7, 2016| language=Japanese}}\n</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-4-04-865809-6}}\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF; text-align: left\"|Tatsuya arrives and neutralizes the anti-magician group. With Miyuki by his side, Tatsuya uses his full powers to search for Jiedo and relay the location to the Yotsuba. The master clans then assemble a unit to capture Jiedo, who is instead killed by the USNA during the mission.\n|-\n<!-- |colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF; text-align: left\"|Plot 19 -->\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |20\n|style=\"text-align: left\"|{{Nihongo foot|South Sea Riot Arc|\u5357\u6d77\u9a12\u64fe\u7de8|Nankai S\u014dj\u014d-hen|group=Jp.}}\n|September 10, 2016<ref name=\"LN 20\">{{cite web|url=http://dengekibunko.jp/newreleases/978-4-04-892318-7/|script-title=ja:\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u52a3\u7b49\u751f(20)| publisher=[[Dengeki Bunko]]| accessdate=September 11, 2016| language=Japanese}}\n</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-4-04-892318-7}}\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF; text-align: left\"|Japan has recently completed an artificial island in Okinawa to mine resources from the ocean. In response, a rebellion cell from the Great Asian Alliance and the Australian military work together to destroy the island in order to keep the world's power in check. The Yotsuba send Tatsuya to pacify the saboteurs and to protect the island. At the same time, the senior class of First High's graduation party is taking place nearby. As the attack on the island commences, members of First High and Tatsuya quell and capture the rebels.\n|-\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |21\n|style=\"text-align: left\"|{{Nihongo foot|Prologue of Disturbance Arc (I)|\u52d5\u4e71\u306e\u5e8f\u7ae0\u7de8<\u4e0a>|D\u014dran no Josh\u014d-hen <J\u014d>|group=Jp.}}\n|February 10, 2017<ref name=\"LN 21\">{{cite web| url=http://dengekibunko.jp/newreleases/978-4-04-892669-0/| script-title=ja:\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u52a3\u7b49\u751f(21)|publisher=[[Dengeki Bunko]]| accessdate=February 8, 2017| language=Japanese}}\n</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-4-04-865809-6}}\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF; text-align: left\"|The Brazilian government's utilization of their strategic magician creates chaos and fear to non-magicians throughout the world, causing a political [[Cold war (general term)|cold war]] to take place. The New Soviet Union mounts an attack on Japan's navy, forcing Tatsuya to intervene. As tensions between the world's superpowers rise, the USNA and New Soviet Union make plans to neutralize Tatsuya.\n|-\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |22\n|style=\"text-align: left\"|{{Nihongo foot|Prologue of Disturbance Arc (II)|\u52d5\u4e71\u306e\u5e8f\u7ae0\u7de8<\u4e0b>|D\u014dran no Josh\u014d-hen <Ge>|group=Jp.}}\n|June 9, 2017<ref name=\"LN 22\">{{cite web| url=http://dengekibunko.jp/newreleases/978-4-04-892949-3/| script-title=ja:\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u52a3\u7b49\u751f(22)|publisher=[[Dengeki Bunko]]| accessdate=April 7, 2017| language=Japanese}}\n</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-4-04-892949-3}}\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF; text-align: left\" |The Tooyama clan, a magician branch loyal to the government, evaluate Tatsuya as a threat. Several [[black operation|black ops]] led by Tsukasa Tooyama are used to assess Tatsuya's abilities and to determine a countermeasure should he become an enemy of the country. In retaliation, Tatsuya is ordered by Maya to break into the Tooyama stronghold and to free the captured USNA soldiers based within Japan; he succeeds and Tooyama ends her operations, having discovered the Jumonji clan can stop Tatsuya.\n|-\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |23\n|style=\"text-align: left\"|{{Nihongo foot|Isolation Arc|\u5b64\u7acb\u7de8|Koritsu-hen|group=Jp.}}\n|August 10, 2017<ref name=\"LN 23\">{{cite web| url=http://dengekibunko.jp/newreleases/978-4-04-893281-3/| script-title=ja:\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u52a3\u7b49\u751f\uff0823\uff09|publisher=[[Dengeki Bunko]]| accessdate=December 24, 2017| language=Japanese}}\n</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-4-04-893281-3}}\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |24\n|style=\"text-align: left\"|{{Nihongo foot|Escape Arc (I)|\u30a8\u30b9\u30b1\u30fc\u30d7\u7de8<\u4e0a>|Esuk\u0113pu-hen <J\u014d>|group=Jp.}}\n|March 10, 2018<ref name=\"LN 24\">{{cite web| url=https://dengekibunko.jp/product/mahouka/321712000048.html| script-title=ja:\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u52a3\u7b49\u751f\uff0824\uff09|pub