ki Daioh]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=August 4, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| Visitor Arc\n|Gin Amau\n|GFantasy\n|December 2015\u2013<br>September 2019<ref name=\"Vistor Manga end\">{{cite web |title=The Irregular at Magic High School: Raih\u014dsha-hen Manga Ends in 7th Volume |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-08-17/the-irregular-at-magic-high-school-raihosha-hen-manga-ends-in-7th-volume/.135418 |website=Anime News Network |accessdate=17 August 2018}}</ref>\n|7\n|July 2016\u2013<br>September 2019<ref name=\"The Irregular at Magic High School: Visitor Arc\">{{cite web| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190921162228/https://magazine.jp.square-enix.com/gfantasy/story/mahouka_raihou/| archivedate=September 21, 2019| url=https://magazine.jp.square-enix.com/gfantasy/story/mahouka_raihou/|  title=''The Irregular at Magic High School: Visitor Arc''| publisher=[[Square Enix]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=September 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| Double Seven Arc\n|Tsuna Kitaumi\n|GFantasy\n|October 2016\u2013<br>Summer 2019<ref name=\"DB7M end\">{{cite web |title=The Irregular at Magic High School: Double Seven Manga Ends in 3rd Volume |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-07-27/the-irregular-at-magic-high-school-double-seven-manga-ends-in-3rd-volume/.134761 |website=Anime News Network |accessdate=17 August 2018}}</ref>\n|3\n|?\u2013<br>Spring 2019<ref name=\"DB7M end\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| President Election Arc\n|Yuzuki N Dash\n|Dengeki Daioh\n|June 2018\u2013<br>Ongoing<ref name=\"PresEM announced\">{{cite web|title=Irregular at Magic High School's 'President Election Arc' Manga Approaches Climax|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-08-27/irregular-at-magic-high-school-president-election-arc-manga-approaches-climax/.135970|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=7 October 2018}}</ref>\n|1\n|\u2014\n|-\n|}\n\n====''The Honor Student at Magic High School''====\nA [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] manga titled {{Nihongo4|''The Honor Student at Magic High School''|\u9b54\u6cd5\u79d1\u9ad8\u6821\u306e\u512a\u7b49\u751f|Mah\u014dka K\u014dk\u014d no Y\u016bt\u014dsei}} by Yu Mori premiered in ''Dengeki Daioh''{{'}}s June 2012 issue.<ref name=\"Dengeki 0612\">{{cite web| url=http://www.fujisan.co.jp/product/7773/b/783421/| title=''Dengeki Daioh'' June 2012 issue| publisher=Fujisan.co.jp| language=Japanese| accessdate=August 4, 2015}}</ref> It is currently ongoing, and was collected into seven ''tank\u014dbon'' volumes under the Dengeki Comics Next imprint.<ref name=\"Official Honor Student website\">{{cite web| url=http://daioh.dengeki.com/contents/mahoka/| title=Official ''The Honor Student at Magic High School'' website| publisher=[[Dengeki Daioh]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=August 4, 2015}}</ref> [[Yen Press]] licensed the series' ''tank\u014dbon'' volumes for a North American release, and released the first volume in November 2015.<ref name=\"Yen Press Honor License\">{{cite web| url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-03-09/yen-press-confirms-mahoka-koko-no-yutosei-manga-license/.85783| title=Yen Press Confirms ''Mah\u014dka K\u014dk\u014d no Y\u016bt\u014dsei'' Manga License| date=March 9, 2015| publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| accessdate=August 4, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Hachette Honor 1\">{{cite web| url=http://www.hachettebookgroup.com/titles/tsutomu-sato/the-honor-student-at-magic-high-school-vol-1/9780316351416/| title=''The Honor Student at Magic High School'' Vol. 1| publisher=[[Hachette Book Group]]| accessdate=August 4, 2015| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150810071825/http://www.hachettebookgroup.com/titles/tsutomu-sato/the-honor-student-at-magic-high-school-vol-1/9780316351416/#| archive-date=2015-08-10| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=====Volume list=====\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n | Language        = Japanese\n | SecondLanguage  = English\n | LineColor       = 03379c\n | WithTitle       = no\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 1\n | R